{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\n`CLAUDE_CODE_SESSION_ID` is exposed as an env var ONLY in the remote/cloud runner; the LOCAL\nClaude Code CLI does not export it. Without a shim the session-provenance feature silently\nno-ops for local-CLI users â€” the most common case. The robust, harness-agnostic capture is a\nClaude Code SessionStart hook that reads the hook's `session_id` from stdin and exports it as\nthe portable `REBAR_SESSION_ID`, plus the harness tag `AI_AGENT=claude-code`.\n\n## What\n- **Hook script (`scripts/session-shims/claude-code-session-start.sh`).** Reads the\n  SessionStart JSON envelope from stdin (field `session_id`) and, when `CLAUDE_ENV_FILE` is\n  set, APPENDS `export REBAR_SESSION_ID=<id>` and `export AI_AGENT=<tag>` to it (the documented\n  Claude Code env-injection mechanism â€” append with `>>` so other hooks' vars survive). The\n  harness tag follows the established `AI_AGENT` vocabulary: the base name `claude-code`,\n  suffixed with `_<version>` (e.g. `claude-code_1.2.3`) when `CLAUDE_CODE_VERSION` is available,\n  else bare `claude-code`. Uses `python3` (already a rebar dependency) to parse the JSON\n  robustly â€” any parse failure, a missing/blank `session_id`, or an absent `CLAUDE_ENV_FILE` is\n  a silent no-op with exit 0 (fire-and-forget; NEVER blocks the session). Idempotent: re-firing\n  on resume/clear/compact re-exports the same value (last export wins).\n- **Vocabulary alignment.** Update the `claude-code_<ver>` examples in `docs/config.md`,\n  `docs/event-schema.md`, and the `session_id.py` comment to present the harness tag as a base\n  name with an OPTIONAL `_<version>` suffix, so bare `claude-code` is consistent with the\n  documented vocabulary.\n- **Docs (`docs/session-id-shims.md`).** A new install guide: the `settings.json`\n  `hooks.SessionStart` snippet pointing at the script, the caveat that the id is NOT stable\n  across `--resume`/`--continue`/fork/subagents (epic gotcha G1 â€” treat it as \"the session\n  that emitted the claim event\"), and guidance to keep it session-scoped (do NOT export\n  `REBAR_SESSION_ID` from a shell profile â€” gotcha G3). Cross-links `docs/config.md`.\n\n## Scope\n- IN: the Claude Code SessionStart hook script, the `docs/session-id-shims.md` install page,\n  the small vocabulary-alignment doc/comment edits (`docs/config.md`, `docs/event-schema.md`,\n  `session_id.py`), and a unit test validating the script (valid shell + env-file output for\n  mock stdin, version, malformed, and no-op cases).\n- OUT: Codex/Cursor shims (S6 / 7656, which extend the same docs page); the record/read core\n  (S1-S3, S5).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `scripts/session-shims/claude-code-session-start.sh` exists and is valid shell. Proof:\n      `bash -n scripts/session-shims/claude-code-session-start.sh` (asserted in\n      `tests/unit/test_session_shims.py`).\n- [ ] Given stdin `{\"session_id\":\"abc123\"}` and a `CLAUDE_ENV_FILE` temp path, the script\n      writes `export REBAR_SESSION_ID=abc123` AND `export AI_AGENT=claude-code` to that file;\n      with `CLAUDE_CODE_VERSION=1.2.3` set it writes `export AI_AGENT=claude-code_1.2.3`. Proof:\n      `pytest tests/unit/test_session_shims.py -k \"claude_code_exports or version\" -q`.\n- [ ] Robust no-op (exit 0, empty env file, never blocks the session) for each of: a\n      blank/missing `session_id`, MALFORMED/unparseable JSON on stdin, and an unset\n      `CLAUDE_ENV_FILE`. Proof: `pytest tests/unit/test_session_shims.py -k \"noop or malformed\" -q`.\n- [ ] `docs/session-id-shims.md` documents the hook script path + `settings.json` install\n      snippet, the G1 id-instability caveat, and the session-scoped (not-in-profile) guidance.\n      Proof: a doc-content assert in `test_session_shims.py` that checks for the literal strings\n      `SessionStart`, `scripts/session-shims/claude-code-session-start.sh`, `REBAR_SESSION_ID`,\n      `resume`, `subagents`, and `profile`.\n- [ ] The `claude-code_<ver>` vocabulary examples in `docs/config.md`, `docs/event-schema.md`,\n      and `session_id.py` are updated to a base-name + optional `_<version>` form (so bare\n      `claude-code` is consistent). Proof: `pytest tests/unit/test_harness_provenance.py -k docs -q`\n      still green.\n\n## Depends on\n- S1 (the `REBAR_SESSION_ID` contract) and S5 (the `AI_AGENT` -> `claim_harness` contract)."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783547603061927001,"uuid":"40f680a6-d122-40ba-b9fc-8ccde14290af"}